\f0\fs24 \cf0 # `lv` Tool Reference \'97 for the Ninox Diagnostic Tool\
\
`lv` is an in-house CLI on Ninox production database hosts. It manages on-disk LevelDB databases. This document is the reference for an automation tool that drives `lv` remotely via `tsh ssh`.\
\
## Environment\
\
- **Driver machine:** operator's Mac\
- **Transport:** Teleport (`tsh ssh apollo@<host> "<remote command>"`)\
- **Remote user:** `apollo` (read-only)\
- **Cluster proxy:** `teleport.ninox.de`\
- **Hosts:** ~1000, listed by `tsh ls`. Each host = one customer workspace.\
\
## Path convention (verified on host `zeppelin`)\
\
```\
/var/nxdb/accounts/<account-id>/db/<db-id>/data/        # live database\
/var/nxdb/accounts/<account-id>/snapshot/<db-id>/<ts>/data/   # snapshots\
```\
\
- One host has multiple accounts (e.g., 15 on `zeppelin`).\
- Each account has multiple databases under `db/`.\
- Snapshots under `snapshot/` are historical and out of scope for diagnostics.\
- Watch out for accounts named `undefined` \'97 these are corrupt/orphaned, skip in the UI.\
\
A LevelDB directory is recognised by containing a file named `CURRENT`.\
\
To enumerate all live DBs on a host:\
```\
tsh ssh apollo@<host> "find /var/nxdb/accounts -maxdepth 4 -path '*/db/*/data' -name 'data' -type d"\
```\
\
## Hard rules\
\
1. **Read-only.** Every `lv` invocation MUST pass `--readonly`. No exceptions.\
2. **Allowlisted subcommands only.** Permitted: `diagnose`, `report`, `stats`, `tables`, `validate`, `orphans`, `schema`, `metrics`, `sizes`, `keys`, `search`, `history`, `version`, `analyze`, `views`.\
3. **Forbidden subcommands** (must never be invoked by the tool, even via user input): `repair`, `compact`, `strip-field`, `purge-history`, `backup`, `generate`, `export`, `export-history`, `get`, `repl`.\
4. **`--json` preferred** wherever the command supports it.\
5. **Timeout every call.** Default 60s per `lv` call; `lv report` and `--deep` get 5 minutes.\
\
## Output formats\
\
### `lv diagnose --readonly --json <path>`\
Returns a JSON object with shape:\
```json\
\{\
  "path": "...",\
  "status": "ok" | "warning" | "fail",\
  "isLocked": bool,\
  "isAccessible": bool,\
  "checks": [\{"name": str, "status": "pass"|"warn"|"fail", "message": str\}, ...],\
  "info": \{ ... \},\
  "warnings": [str, ...]\
\}\
```\
Severity mapping: any `checks[].status == "fail"` \uc0\u8594  red. Else any `"warn"` or top-level `status == "warning"` \u8594  amber. Else green.\
\
A locked database is normal (live customer DB) \'97 surface as info, not amber.\
\
### `lv report --readonly -o <dir> --name <name> <path>`\
Writes two files to `<dir>`:\
- `<name>-report.md` \'97 human-readable, optimized for LLM consumption\
- `<name>-report.json` \'97 full structured data\
\
Run time: typically 2\'9630s, longer on big DBs. Use `--skip-metrics` for speed if needed.\
\
### `lv stats --readonly --json <path>`\
LevelDB internals: LSM tree, compaction, write delay. Useful for performance triage.\
\
### `lv tables --readonly <path>`\
Human-friendly table list with record counts and sizes. (May or may not support `--json` \'97 verify.)\
\
### `lv validate --readonly --check-schema --check-references --json --limit 100 <path>`\
Data integrity. Important for "customer says records are missing/broken" tickets.\
\
### Less-used but allowlisted\
- `lv orphans` \'97 broken references\
- `lv schema` \'97 schema dump\
- `lv sizes` \'97 per-record size analysis\
- `lv keys` \'97 key listing (do not dump full DB; always use `--limit`)\
- `lv metrics` \'97 Ninox-specific metrics\
\
